Fed’s Kocherlakota Says Next 4 Or 5 Years to Be Very Challenging

-- B y   V i v i e n   L o u   C h e n
-- 
2011-10-21T18:50:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/fed-s-kocherlakota-says-next-4-or-5-years-to-be-very-challenging.html
Federal Reserve Bank of  Minneapolis 
President Narayana Kocherlakota said today that the future
looks bright while the next four or five years will be “very
challenging.”  Kocherlakota, answering audience questions after a speech
at the Harvard Club of  Minnesota  in Minneapolis, said that it is
“very troubling” how long the recovery is taking.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivien Lou Chen in  San Francisco  at 
 vchen1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  